metadata.name: CrossWorlds #238
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Plottable Memories: Train Station #67
metadata.description:
'Memories: Train Station' explores plottable abstract photography composition around the "Train Station" theme. Memories can be blurry, faded and abstract and the strokes texturing aim to reflect that.

Many images are used as primitive to make the plot texture. The work is very generative and have great range of variety thanks to the many effects combined together. Photos has been taken by @greweb in Paris' "Gare de l'Est" train station.

Traits of the art includes a suggested "Title" that is self-generated.

PLOTTABLE?!

A SVG file can be exported (right click save) to plot the piece physically. The plot is made of up to 200 000 points – making it time consuming to produce. It is recommended to optimize the pen travel. Inks can have surprising outcomes when done physically.

The digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors – as long as NFT is owned at request time.

More details and Source code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-memories-train-station

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Bonsai Bonanza #741
metadata.description:
In previous works, I was attracted by the idea of ​​the domestication of plants.
According to Wikipedia, the purposes of bonsai are primarily contemplation for the viewer, and the pleasant exercise of effort and ingenuity for the grower. By contrast with other plant cultivation practices, bonsai is not intended for production of food or for medicine. Instead, bonsai practice focuses on long-term cultivation and shaping of one or more small trees growing in a container.
I pressume that the main intention is aesthetic. The beauty. Because we love beautiful things.
It is very interesting how we modify certain creatures for our sake of satisfaction.

May this collection brings you good fortune.

metadata.name: CityScape: Istanbul #48
metadata.description:
Istanbul is a city that straddles the Bosporus Strait, and lies in both Europe and Asia, with a population of over 15 million residents. Most of the population is located in big iconic hills known as the "Seven Hills of Istanbul". 

   In this project, I tried to capture and interpret the daily life routine of the people who live in these hills with the viewing point from Bosphorus. There are three camera angle possibilities to examine the details in different layers. Also, building types, the slope of the hill, and green area density vary in between those scenarios. There are two time zones: day and night. In the night scene, there is a possibility to obtain the crescent moon which is the symbol of the culture inhabits in these lands.

To save as a high-quality image, open in live view and click yes on the incoming prompt.

Created with p5js

metadata.name: Highrise of Homes #48
metadata.description:
Highrise of Homes project is a "vertical community" to "accommodate people's conflicting desires to enjoy the cultural advantages of an urban center, without sacrificing the private home identity and garden space associated with suburbia."

Buy a cozy cottage in our steel constructed choice lots, less than a mile above Broadway, only ten minutes by elevator. All the comforts of the country with none of its disadvantages.

[Mouse Move]
- Zoomed View.

[Mouse Click]
- Focus/Unfocus to Zoomed View.

[r]
- Random Scene.

[s]
- At Main Screen: Save with 2200x2200 px.
- At Focused Screens: Save with window size.

metadata.name: Labyrinth #109
metadata.description:
The beginning of life is an incessant dream, a kaleidoscope of surprising discoveries, a colorful labyrinth in which you are enclosed by indefinitely high walls or a void, which you have to pass on your own. The person who may later become a guide through the labyrinth is still hiding behind some wall, past another turn. The main goal is to find him. If you succeed...


But you will succeed.


© Victoria Crux, 2022

metadata.name: Shattered Obelisks #103
metadata.description:
Shattered Obelisks began as a work that is dedicated to my habit of mindlessly drawing on paper when I am stressed, depressed or immersed in difficult thoughts.

Like a patient undergoing psychotherapy and piecing together the causes of unconscious fears and anxieties, I and my artwork have assembled ourselves into something shaped, found order in the chaos and separated it from the external noise.

It took 3 months of continuous, obsessive work. I have developed a huge library, designed for hand-like drawing. The functionality of this library is four times larger than what is shown in this drop.

I plan to put this library out into the public domain when I deem it complete, and hope that it will help someone express themselves through the creative process as much as it helped for me.

In case you've encountered a problem with inverted colours, try changing browser or disabling extensions. This problem only occurred once during testing on a massive amount of devices and was resolved by disabling extensions.

IMPORTANT NOTES BLOCK:

NOTE 1: This artwork should be viewed at a browser scale of 100%. Reducing the scale will increase the amount of detail, but may unpredictably affect the preservation of the location of secondary objects.

NOTE 2: This work can be printed on a plotter. Click S for saving it in .SVG.
Detailed instructions and answers to possible questions can be found in the console output of the code.

NOTE 3: This drop is the first one from the series of 3. It will be used as AL ticket in next drops of this series.

@abakshonokoleg
